===========================================================
      SENSOR GUI ON RASPBERRY PI 5 - SETUP GUIDE
===========================================================
This guide covers the installation and execution of the 
Sensor GUI for BMP280/BH1750 sensors and Camera Module 3.

-----------------------------------------------------------
1. PRE-REQUISITES
-----------------------------------------------------------

OS & SYSTEM:
* OS: Raspbian OS Trixie (2025-12-04-raspios-trixie-arm64-full.img)
* Hardware: Raspberry Pi 5
* Enabled Interfaces: I2C, UART, and SSH
  (Use 'sudo raspi-config' > Interface Options to enable)

HARDWARE CONNECTIONS:
* I2C Sensors: Connect BMP280 and BH1750 to I2C-1
  - SDA: GPIO 2 (Pin 3)
  - SCL: GPIO 3 (Pin 5)
* Camera: Raspberry Pi Camera Module 3 (connected to CAM/DISP port)

SYSTEM PACKAGES:
$ sudo apt update
$ sudo apt install rpi-libcamera-apps python3-venv python3-pip

-----------------------------------------------------------
2. ENVIRONMENT SETUP
-----------------------------------------------------------

1. Create Project Directory:
   $ mkdir ~/acms_prj
   $ cd ~/acms_prj

2. Initialize Python Virtual Environment:
   (The --system-site-packages flag ensures access to system camera libs)
   $ python3 -m venv --system-site-packages env
   $ source env/bin/activate

3. Install Python Dependencies:
   $ pip install PyQt6 Picamera2 smbus2 numpy

-----------------------------------------------------------
3. FILE STRUCTURE & EXECUTION
-----------------------------------------------------------

1. Setup GUI Directory:
   $ mkdir gui

2. Copy source files into the gui folder:
   $ cp <source_path>/sensor_gui.py gui/
   $ cp <source_path>/sensors_data.py gui/

3. Ensure scripts are executable:
   $ chmod +x gui/sensor_gui.py

4. Run the GUI:
   $ python3 gui/sensor_gui.py

-----------------------------------------------------------
NOTES:
* Ensure your Camera Module 3 is detected using: rpicam-hello --list-cameras
* If I2C sensors are not detected, run: i2cdetect -y 1
===========================================================

